Privacy Policy - en
1. Introduction
This Privacy Policy aims to inform you about the types of personal data we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding this data. By using our site, you accept the practices described in this policy.
2. Data Collection
We collect personal data that you provide directly to us, such as your name, email address, and other information when you register for our service or contact us. We may also automatically collect data through cookies and other tracking technologies.
3. Data Usage
The personal data collected is used to:
Manage your account and provide our services.
Communicate with you, particularly to respond to your requests.
Improve our site and personalize your user experience.
Analyze site usage through analytics tools.
4. Cookies
4.1 What is a Cookie?
A cookie is a small text file stored on your device when you visit a website. Cookies allow us to recognize your device and remember certain information about your preferences or past actions.
4.2 Types of Cookies Used
We use the following types of cookies:
Essential Cookies:
These cookies are necessary for the proper functioning of the site and cannot be disabled in our systems. They are typically set in response to actions you take, such as logging in or filling out forms.
Performance Cookies:
These cookies allow us to measure and analyze site usage to improve its performance.
Functionality Cookies:
These cookies enable enhanced functionality and personalization of the site, such as remembering your preferences.
Targeting/Advertising Cookies:
These cookies are used to display relevant advertisements based on your interests.
4.3 Cookie Consent
During your first visit to our site, a cookie banner appears to inform you about cookie usage. You can accept or refuse non-essential cookies through this banner. Your consent is stored for 6 months, after which you will be asked again.
4.4 Cookie Management
You can configure your browser to block or delete cookies. However, some features of our site may not work properly if you disable cookies.
5. Data Sharing
We do not share your personal data with third parties, except in the following cases:
When necessary to provide a service you have requested.
When we have obtained your explicit consent.
To comply with legal obligations.
6. Your Rights
In accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), you have the following rights regarding your personal data:
Right of access: You have the right to request access to your personal data that we hold.
Right to rectification: You have the right to request correction of inaccurate or incomplete personal data.
Right to erasure: You can request the deletion of your personal data in certain circumstances.
Right to portability: You have the right to request the transfer of your personal data to another service.
Right to object: You can object to the processing of your personal data under certain conditions.
To exercise these rights, please contact us at contact@kenantech.com.
7. Changes to Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with an update date. We encourage you to regularly review this page to stay informed about how we protect your data.
